<keyLead box="[136,1450,793,815]" pageId="5" pageNumber="277">
14a. Leaves distichous; pistillate inflorescences spicate; tepals of the pistillate flowers free; stigmas 2 equal ............................... 
<taxonomicName box="[1385,1450,793,814]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Moraceae" genus="Morus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="5" pageNumber="277" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1385,1450,793,814]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="277">Morus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[136,1452,159,872]" pageId="5" pageNumber="277">
<keyLead pageId="5" pageNumber="277">
14b. Leaves spirally arranged or subopposite; pistillate inflorescences globose; tepals of the pistillate flowers connate; stigma 1, or if 2, then unequal 
<emphasis box="[334,1451,850,872]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="277">
........................................................................................................................................... 
<taxonomicName box="[1170,1301,850,871]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Moraceae" genus="Broussonetia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="5" pageNumber="277" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
